Best Kodi Skins for Firestick, Android TV, & More (Updated 2024)

March 28, 2024 / Kodi

Tell your friends about this!

If you are looking for the Best Kodi Skins, you’ve come to the right place as this guide presents an updated list of all the best skin options for Kodi users on nearly any device.

Kodi is an Open Source Media platform with tons of Settings, Features, and more to host and view your favorite content. This includes the ability to install various Addons and Builds that provide this content in a sleek user interface.

The user interface within Kodi is referred to as the “Skin” and there are tons of options to choose from. These vary in overall layout, size, and much more which will allow you to customize the home screen of your application for a personalized viewing experience.

In fact, installing a new Skin on your Kodi platform may allow you to add widgets and much more to create a Custom Kodi Build with all of your preferred content in one location.

The official Kodi Repository has various Skins to choose from which are extremely easy to download and install. However, there are also other Skin options to choose from that developers have created and we provide both options in our list below.

Choosing a Skin is based entirely on personal preference and we suggest testing a few and seeing what you like before settling on one. If you aren’t happy with any of them, you can always revert back to the original Skin which is the Estuary Kodi Skin.

The following guide will help you make your Skin selection a little easier with an up-to-date list of the Best Kodi Skins. We also provide step-by-step instructions to install these including those that must be downloaded with a repository URL.

Table of Contents [Show]

    How to Install Kodi Skin

    Official Skin Options

    There are tons of fabulous options available within the official Kodi Repository that you can easily install with just a few clicks.

    1. Click the Settings Icon.

    2. Click Interface.

    3. Choose Skin.

    4. Click Get more…

    5. Choose from the list of provided Skins.

    Enjoy!

    3rd Party Skin Options

    If you are using a 3rd party Skin, a few other steps are required. This is the same method used to install 3rd party Kodi Addons, Builds, and more.

    1. Select Settings.

    2. Click File Manager.

    3. Choose Add Source.

    4. Click None.

    5. Enter the repository URL for your Skin choice and click OK.

    6. Type a name for the media source and click OK.

    7. Click Add-ons.

    8. Choose install from zip file.

    9. Choose your media source.

    10. Select the zip file.

    11. You will see the Repository add-on installed message.

    12. Click install from repository.

    13. Choose your repo.

    14. Select Look and feel.

    15. Click Skin.

    16. Choose your Skin.

    Enjoy!

    Best Kodi Skins

    Arctic: Zephyr – Reloaded

    The most popular Kodi Skin is Arctic: Zephyr – Reloaded with its app-like layout and easy-to-use category/widget options. With the scroll bar at the bottom, your content is displayed in clear view with large posters and much more.

    It can easily be installed from the official Kodi repository so you don’t have to worry about sideloading Arctic Zephyr and can get to streaming instantly!

    Fentastic

    3rd Party Skin

    This skin was based around the popular FEN Kodi Addon, however, it works perfectly with nearly any addon choices that you prefer. The design uses the original Estuary layout but with widget capabilities which makes it extremely fast on any device you prefer.

    Use the Repository URL below to install Fentastic on your Kodi device.

    https://ivarbrandt.github.io/repository.ivarbrandt/

    Arctic Horizon 2

    3rd Party Skin

    This sleek, futuristic-looking skin packs a punch with information displayed both vertically and horizontally. The developer keeps it updated so that bugs are fixed and repaired which means it is always running at peak performance.

    With widget capabilities and extremely fast navigation, Arctic Horizon 2 is one you will want to give a try if you are looking to upgrade your Kodi interface.

    https://jurialmunkey.github.io/repository.jurialmunkey/

    Confluence

    A long withstanding skin, Confluence features an easy-to-use menu bar that is great for those browsing categories. It is used in tons of Kodi Builds due to its simplicity and easy-to-navigate widget options that provide the best content.

    Those who want a personalized layout can edit items such as background images

    Aeon Nox: SiLVO

    The Aeon Nox Skin is another extremely popular Kodi skin because of its simplicity and futuristic feel. With recent updates, it is now named Aeon Nox: SiLVO.

    This skin has been used in plenty of Kodi Builds including the ever-popular No Limits Magic Build which has stood the test of time. If installing the Aeon Nox Skin, make sure to allow enough time for sub-menu items to build as this option is larger than other choices in this list.

    Amber

    The Amber Skin is great for those who want to customize their home screen with widgets and more.

    With Amber, you can change the main menu to show any pictures you want by simply uploading them to your device. Users can also edit the Settings tabs to show horizontally or vertically, along with many other awesome features.

    Mimic – LR

    Mimic is a clean-looking Skin that looks similar to the original Estuary Skin with a few added components.

    You are able to change the Skin’s fonts, background, and much more. Because it is so light in size, Mimic works great on all streaming devices, especially the Amazon Firestick/Fire TV which are the most popular media players available.

    Unity

    Unity is an easy-to-use option that works fabulously on any Kodi device. It was based on the Confluence Skin but is more catered towards Kids and novice users with a simple layout/design.

    Those who use Android TV/Google TV devices will likely notice the similarity it provides to these user-interfaces, however, Unity has tons of Settings and features that we can adjust to display exactly what we are looking for.

    Arctic Fuse

    3rd Party Kodi Skin

    Another high-powered, 3rd party Kodi skin that keeps many Kodi users happy is Arctic Fuse which was created by the same developers as Arctic Horizon. You will notice a similar design, and quick navigation that packs a punch.

    Content options are easy to find with the vertical navigation menu which display all of your favorites and can easily be added or adjusted with Widget capabilities. This is one you need to give a try!

    https://ivarbrandt.github.io/repository.ivarbrandt/

    Pellucid

    Simplicity is the best way to describe the Pellucid Kodi Skin. An extremely clean interface with a high-quality background is why Pellucid continues to be one of the most used Skins available.

    Categories are listed in the middle of the screen with small settings logos on the bottom which make for an extremely efficient layout.

    Bello 9

    This newest version of Bello Kodi skin is a good example of minimalism and functionality as it has reached “Level 9”.

    Users like the colorful interface and the organized add-ons that make it easy to search for movies, music, images and other content. The oversized red cursor and menu icons are also a treat for those who prefer emphasized visuals.

    Users can also filter content easily by typing in words related to title and description or they can look into categories such as Most Popular, Latest Movies, and Box Office Films among others.

    AppTV

    Those who have owned or used an Apple TV device will see exactly why this skin is titled AppTV. The layout is similar and browsing for content is a breeze with simple icon options to choose from such as Movies, TV Shows, Music, Weather, and more.

    Quartz

    Quartz is a must-have for your Kodi skin library. It’s another fan-art-based Kodi skin design that is highly customizable, with various tab/widget options that cater to the end user.

    Its lightweight design and simple menu bar make it enjoyable for all levels of Kodi users from beginners to experts and everyone in between. It works fabulously on any Kodi device including Firestick and Android TV/Google TV Boxes.

    Rapier

    The clean and no-nonsense design best describes Rapier. The neat and elegant interface features customer home items, clear icons, splash screen, audio DSP support, games support, and touch support.

    Although the entire look and feel lean towards a classic interface, it also shares similar features found in other skins. For example, when navigating on the interface, additional information is displayed every time a user hovers over an icon.

    fTV

    One of the longest active skins on Kodi is fTV by hitcher. Many users enjoy this skin because it’s replicated based on the Firestick/Fire TV interface.  If you’re using one of these devices, fTV is the perfect companion. The simple controls allow users to switch access from photos to TV shows instantly.

    Eminence

    This lightweight skin is extremely easy to use yet has a modern design for users looking for an up-to-date interface.

    Those who stream movies and TV shows prefer the practicality of the design since it does not have fancy icons that distract users. The text of movie synopses and related information are easily recognizable, making every selection much easier.

    In addition, all menu items fit in the screen making the vertical menu more convenient for users.

    Aeon Tajo

    Aeon Tajo is a must-have for your Kodi skin library. It was inspired by the Aeon Nox 5 Skin which is no longer available. If you are a Movie lover, you will enjoy browsing content with Aeon Tajo that displays huge posters and detailed synopsis info.

    You can easily navigate the category/widget options and adjust them to your personal preference for a custom Kodi streaming experience.

    Features & Details

    With your preferred Skin now in place, there are a few other visual settings you can change within the software. If you would like to edit the background, font, and more, this can easily be done within Interface Settings.

    A few options include changing themes, colors, and zoom. By editing these, you can cater to the background of your Kodi platform to look exactly how you want. I suggest playing around with these options until you are happy with how the Kodi screen looks.

    If you are looking for an easy way to set up Kodi, you can also install a Kodi Build. With a build, Kodi’s best add-ons are pre-installed along with Skin Settings and more so you can quickly begin streaming.

    If you have a favorite Kodi Skin that is not featured in this list, let us know using the Comment Section below!
